Sentencas: Nickel with yttria stabilised zirconia (Ni-YSZ) is usually used as anode material for the solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) technology.
Titulo: Impact of 'redox' cycles on performances of solid oxide fuel cells: Case of the electrolyte supported cells

Sentencas: Upon cyclic reduction and oxidation of Ni-YSZ ceramic-metal (cermet), the induced cell degradation constitutes one of the main limitations to the SOFCs lifetime.
Titulo: Impact of 'redox' cycles on performances of solid oxide fuel cells: Case of the electrolyte supported cells

Sentencas: In this study, the effect of anode reduction and oxidation cycling on typical electrolyte supported cell (ESC) has been investigated.
Titulo: Impact of 'redox' cycles on performances of solid oxide fuel cells: Case of the electrolyte supported cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical degradation has been followed by impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Impact of 'redox' cycles on performances of solid oxide fuel cells: Case of the electrolyte supported cells

Sentencas: The cell damage has been characterised after testing with scanning electron microscopy (SEM).
Titulo: Impact of 'redox' cycles on performances of solid oxide fuel cells: Case of the electrolyte supported cells

Sentencas: It has been shown that cells can withstand several 'redox' cycles without major decrease in electrochemical performances.
Titulo: Impact of 'redox' cycles on performances of solid oxide fuel cells: Case of the electrolyte supported cells

Sentencas: The 'redox' cycling induces only a slight degradation rate estimated to similar to 70 m Omega cm(2) per cycle.
Titulo: Impact of 'redox' cycles on performances of solid oxide fuel cells: Case of the electrolyte supported cells

Sentencas: The microstructural observations are found to be consistent with the impedance diagram analysis.
Titulo: Impact of 'redox' cycles on performances of solid oxide fuel cells: Case of the electrolyte supported cells

Sentencas: Both reveal that the damage is restricted to bulk cermet microstructure change, whereas no cracking is initiated at the anode/electrolyte interface.
